&ldquo;The great thing about D&rsquo;Angelo is you can coach him,&rdquo; Atkinson said. &ldquo;I was hard on him [Tuesday] in the beginning. A couple bad shots, I called a timeout. A rogue defensive possession, I called another timeout to yell at him.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;He responds. He never comes back at you. He says, &lsquo;OK, coach,&rsquo; and he gets better. That&rsquo;s a pleasure when you have your All-Star that you can coach and accepts coaching and doesn&rsquo;t cop an attitude and accepts it. It&rsquo;s huge. That&rsquo;s leadership.&rdquo;

